----------------------------------------------------------------------
Source data attributions
----------------------------------------------------------------------

This dataset incorporates and is derived from the following public sources.
All consumers must preserve these attributions per ODbL-1.0 §4.3.

  - OpenStreetMap (https://www.openstreetmap.org)
    © OpenStreetMap contributors, licensed ODbL-1.0.
    Used as the topological scaffold (footways, crossings, road centerlines).

  - NYC DOT Pedestrian Ramp Locations (dataset id: ufzp-rrqu)
    https://data.cityofnewyork.us/Transportation/Pedestrian-Ramp-Locations/ufzp-rrqu
    Public domain. Used for curb-ramp geometry, slopes, and condition.

  - NYC Planimetric Database: Sidewalks (dataset id: 52n9-sdep)
    https://data.cityofnewyork.us/City-Government/NYC-Planimetric-Database-Sidewalk/52n9-sdep
    Public domain. Used for sidewalk widths and as a gap-fill source for
    sidewalk centerlines.

  - NYC Borough Boundaries (dataset id: 7t3b-ywvw)
    https://data.cityofnewyork.us/City-Government/Borough-Boundaries/7t3b-ywvw
    Public domain. Used as region polygons (with OSMnx geocoding as a
    fallback when the Socrata dataset is unavailable).

  - NYC 2017 Topobathymetric LiDAR bare-earth DTM (1-foot resolution)
    Served by the NY State GIS Program Office ArcGIS ImageServer
    (https://elevation.its.ny.gov/). Public domain.
    Used to derive node elevations and edge inclines.

  - MTA subway stations with ADA accessibility flags (dataset id: drh3-e2fd,
    with the MTA GTFS static feed as fallback)
    https://data.cityofnewyork.us/resource/drh3-e2fd.json
    Public domain. Used as a transit-accessibility sidecar index.

  - OpenSidewalks Schema v0.3
    https://sidewalks.washington.edu/opensidewalks/0.3/schema.json
    Developed by the Taskar Center for Accessible Technology, University of
    Washington. The schema specifies the OSW feature types and properties to
    which this dataset conforms.

